#. <section class="sutta" id="mn113"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn113:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 113"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 113"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn113:0.2"
msgid "Sappurisasutta"
msgstr "A Good Person"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn113:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn113:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn113:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn113:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn113:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn113:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

# Here it seems "quality" seems better than "teaching" for dhamma. Nevertheless, I wonder whether teaching is not meant even here: the problem is glorifying oneself, which perhaps means in a Dhamma talk?
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn113:2.1"
msgid "“sappurisadhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asappurisadhammañca."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you the qualities of a good person and the "
"qualities of a bad person."

msgctxt "mn113:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn113:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn113:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.38"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn113:3.1"
msgid "“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo?"
msgstr "“And what is a quality of a bad person?"

msgctxt "mn113:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, asappuriso uccākulā pabbajito hoti."
msgstr "Take a bad person who has gone forth from an eminent family."

msgctxt "mn113:3.3"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "They reflect:"

msgctxt "mn113:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ khomhi uccākulā pabbajito, ime panaññe bhikkhū na uccākulā "
"pabbajitā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I have gone forth from an eminent family, unlike these other mendicants.’"

msgctxt "mn113:3.5"
msgid "So tāya uccākulīnatāya attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that."

#. VAR: Ayaṃ → ayampi (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn113:3.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo."
msgstr "This is a quality of a bad person."

msgctxt "mn113:3.7"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "A good person reflects:"

msgctxt "mn113:3.8"
msgid ""
"‘na kho uccākulīnatāya lobhadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, dosadhammā vā "
"parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, mohadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s not because of one’s eminent family that thoughts of greed, hate, or "
"delusion come to an end."

msgctxt "mn113:3.9"
msgid "No cepi uccākulā pabbajito hoti;"
msgstr "Even if someone has not gone forth from an eminent family,"

msgctxt "mn113:3.10"
msgid ""
"so ca hoti dhammānudhammappaṭipanno sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī, so "
"tattha pujjo, so tattha pāsaṃso’ti."
msgstr ""
"if they practice in line with the teaching, practice properly, and live in "
"line with the teaching, they are worthy of honor and praise for that.’"

# antaram karitva is unusual here, normally it yields the expected sense of “hidden within”. Comm is no help.
msgctxt "mn113:3.11"
msgid ""
"So paṭipadaṃyeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya uccākulīnatāya nevattānukkaṃseti na "
"paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""
"Keeping only the practice close to their heart, they don’t glorify "
"themselves and put others down on account of their eminent family."

msgctxt "mn113:3.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (1)"
msgstr "This is a quality of a good person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4-6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn113:4-6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso mahākulā pabbajito hoti … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, take a bad person who has gone forth from a great family …"

msgctxt "mn113:4-6.2"
msgid "mahābhogakulā pabbajito hoti … pe …"
msgstr "from a wealthy family …"

msgctxt "mn113:4-6.3"
msgid "uḷārabhogakulā pabbajito hoti."
msgstr "from an extremely wealthy family."

msgctxt "mn113:4-6.4"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "They reflect:"

msgctxt "mn113:4-6.5"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ khomhi uḷārabhogakulā pabbajito, ime panaññe bhikkhū na uḷārabhogakulā "
