"nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn113:27.10"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (25)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn113:28.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "mn113:28.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "They reflect:"

msgctxt "mn113:28.3"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ khomhi nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā lābhī, ime panaññe bhikkhū "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā na lābhino’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I have attained the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, "
"unlike these other mendicants.’"

msgctxt "mn113:28.4"
msgid ""
"So tāya nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that."

msgctxt "mn113:28.5"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo."
msgstr "This too is a quality of a bad person."

msgctxt "mn113:28.6"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "A good person reflects:"

msgctxt "mn113:28.7"
msgid "‘nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyāpi kho atammayatā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr ""
"‘The Buddha has spoken of not identifying even with the attainment of the "
"dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "mn113:28.8"
msgid "Yena yena hi maññanti tato taṃ hoti aññathā’ti."
msgstr "For however they conceive it, it turns out to be something else.’"

msgctxt "mn113:28.9"
msgid ""
"So atammayataññeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā "
"nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""
"Keeping only non-identification close to their heart, they don’t glorify "
"themselves and put others down on account of their attainment of the "
"dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "mn113:28.10"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (26)"
msgstr "This too is a quality of a good person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.45"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
#. VAR: cassa disvā āsavā → ekacce āsavā (mr)
msgctxt "mn113:29.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ "
"samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati. Paññāya cassa disvā "
"āsavā parikkhīṇā honti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a good person who, going totally beyond the dimension of "
"neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation "
"of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements "
"come to an end."

#. VAR: Ayaṃ → ayaṃ kho (bj, s1-3, km) | ayampi (si) | ayaṃ pi (pts1)
msgctxt "mn113:29.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na kiñci maññati, na kuhiñci maññati, na kenaci "
"maññatī”ti. (27)"
msgstr ""
"This is a mendicant who does not conceive anything, does not conceive "
"regarding anything, does not conceive with anything.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn113:29.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn113:29.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn113:29.5"
msgid "Sappurisasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
